    {
      "id": "c877f976a82d5c1a43af79cd06c1471a0c217f9d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2012-07-24 05:00:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Do not submit\n\nI am puttign a negative mark so that this does nto get accidentally landed.\n\nThe capabilites are disabled by default already (unless gss is enabled, which is unsupported).\n\nLU-1621 is some other problem where the server starts to imagine the clients have all sorts of capabilities they don't really have (as was evidenced by remote client functionality suddenly being enabled when this patch was added).\nReal root cause for the server behavior needs to be identified indeed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "213c86fe2213f4e439d78c6c3983dd58685d78e2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-07-25 02:39:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI do not think so.\n\nCurrently, capa is enabled by default. But it will distinguish client type to determine whether generate and verify capa. For local client, capa should be bypass. But it is just \"should\". We have not tested capa since Lustre-2.0 released. Just as described in LU-1621, we ignore capa process for new changes since Lustre-2.0 released, there may be some potential issues introduced by those patches.\n\nOn the other hand, capa should take effect for remote client. But as I known, nobody use remote client feature on Lustre-2.x yet, and we never test remote client since Lustre-2.0 released. So nobody can guarantee the right behavior.\n\nIn fact, current capa has some known security holds, which cause the capa cannot work as original expectation. We have already re-designed Lustre-capa in original SUN period. But it was never implemented.\n\nhttps://bugzilla.lustre.org/show_bug.cgi?id=18519\n\nSo current capa does not bring security assurance for most use cases, and may introduce potencial bugs. So please consider to land this patch to disable Lustre-capa totally.\n\nThanks!",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
